The paper deals with multi-modal data analysis, which is a topic that spans across several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on topic modeling and the use of HDP, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses querying the contents of one domain given samples of the other, which falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
